n incontinent horse for a week than have to read that paragraph again!\n\n- Diane Ackerman, One Hundred Names for Love: A Stroke, a Marriage, and the Language of Healing\n|\nThe world was collapsing, and the only thing that really mattered to me was that she was alive.\n\n- Rick Riordan, The Last Olympian\n|\nJust that I have loved you, even when I was nothing and no one to you, when you didn’t know my name and barely knew my face.- Leo\n\n- Sherry\n|\nLet me show you how beautiful life is,Let me take away all your pain;Let me rekindle your faith in love,Let me make you believe in magic again!\n\n- Anamika\n|\nWriters seek to create order out of the chaos of everyday life, and to extract meaning from both the tragic and the mundane\n\n- Hope\n|\nQui plussait, plus se tait. French, you know. The more a man knows, the less he talks.\n\n- Madeleine L'Engle, A Wrinkle in Time\n|\nLet us pray now for the future dead. Though we do not yet know their names, we know that there shall be far too many of them.\n\n- Seth\n|\nRemember, any lie you are told, even deliberately, is often a more significant fact than a truth told in all sincerity.\n\n- Halldór Laxness, Under the Glacier\n|\nDon't put off happiness you can have today. Tomorrow is a hope, not a promise\n\n- Debra\n|\nArt is the writer not having control, but the subject having control of the writer.\n\n- Paula\n|\nAuthors do not choose a story to write, the story chooses us.\n\n- Richard\n|\nThe purpose of my faith is to bring me hope without fear. This is not only beneficial for the life to come, but also in this present life as well.\n\n- Reid A. Ashbaucher, How To Understand And Live Your Faith\n|\nWe just sat there and watched the plane pass the island, and it never came back,' he said. 'I could see it on the radar. It makes you feel terrible. Life was cheap in war.\n\n- Laura Hillenbrand, Unbroken: A World War II Story of Survival, Resilience, and Redemption\n|\nAlthough you can’t go back in time and alter your natural level of potential, you can determine how much of that ability you tap into, exploit and develop for the future.\n\n- Steve Backley, The Champion in all of Us: 12 Rules for Success\n|\nI don't mind if you forget me.Having learned my lesson,I never left an impression on anyone.\n\n- Morrissey\n|\nWhile there is tea, there is hope.')\n\n- Arthur\n|\nIf freedom, democracy, and the rights of man are to be preserved through the ages, free men and women must accept the responsibilities that go with their freedoms.\n\n- Ronald\n|\n... I discovered life sometimes has a way of giving you what you need, but not in the form you expect.\n\n- Lisa Kleypas, Sugar Daddy\n|\nWhen you allow the spirit to speak through you and empower it with love, you will discover things you didn't know you knew.\n\n- Charbel\n|\nLong ago, I stopped buying- let alone reading, books that talk about organizational success but fail to emphasize the importance of TRUST\n\n- Assegid Habtewold, The 9 Cardinal Building Blocks: For Continued Success in Leadership\n|\nAlmost nobody dances sober, unless they happen to be insane.\n\n- H.P.\n|\nThe whole secret of a successful life is to find out what is one's destiny to do, and then do it.\n\n- Henry\n|\nOnce someone asked me, 'What do you want to be your epitaph?' So I said, 'Paulo Coelho died when he was alive.\n\n- Paulo Coelho, The Alchemist\n|\nMy head is full of fireand grief and my tongueruns wild, piercedwith shards of glass.\n\n- Federico García Lorca, Three Tragedies: Blood Wedding, Yerma, Bernarda Alba\n|\nPromise me you'll never forget me because if I thought you would, I'd never leave.\n\n- A.A.\n|\nIf books are not good company, where shall I find it?\n\n- Mark\n|\nIt is your responsibility to find fault with me, it is mine to hear you out. But don't expect me to change.\n\n- John Irving, A Prayer for Owen Meany\n|\nYesterday was just the tip of the iceberg of awesomeness. Things will get better. Keep smiling, don't give up just yet. Perseverance has an amazing gift for you, just wait you see.\n\n- Janna\n|\nThe life you have left is a gift. Cherish it. Enjoy it now, to the fullest. Do what matters, now.\n\n- Leo\n|\nThose who educate children well are more to be honored than they who produce them; for these only gave them life, those the art of living well.\n\n- Aristotle\n|\nI was never more hated than when I tried to be honest. Or when, even as just now I've tried to articulate exactly what I felt to be the truth. No one was satisfied\n\n- Ralph Ellison, Invisible Man\n|\nLife was meant to be lived, and curiosity must be kept alive. One must never, for whatever reason, turn his back on life.\n\n- Eleanor\n|\nNo matter who you are, no matter what you did, no matter where you've come from, you can always change, become a better version of yourself.\n\n- Madonna\n|\nWhen it comes to the core of who we are, it takes incredible effort to shift more than one standard deviation from the mean of your life.\n\n- E.\n|\nThis wolf-woman Self must have freedom to move, to speak, to be angry, and to create.\n\n- Clarissa Pinkola Estés, Women Who Run With the Wolves: Myths and Stories of the Wild Woman Archetype\n|\nWe speak, but it is God who teaches.\n\n- Augustine\n|\nWhen we give ourselves permission to go wherever our outlandish thoughts take us, we feel that rush of creativity and excitement.\n\n- Teresa R. Funke, Bursts of Brilliance for a Creative Life blog\n|\nI think of myself as a bad writer with big ideas, but I'd rather be that than a big writer with bad ideas.\n\n- Michael Moorcock, Elric: The Stealer of Souls\n|\nSometimes we place faith in the wrong people for the right reasons. We're too blind to their faults, and they're too blind to appreciate us.—Brighton Hayes\n\n- Kelli McCracken, Heartstrings\n|\nThere was something about other people's grief that was so exposing, so personal, that she felt she shouldn't be looking.\n\n- Jane Fallon, Getting Rid Of Matthew\n|\nI would rather have 30 minutes of 'wonderful' than a lifetime of nothing special.\n\n- Julia\n|\nThe Bible is not my book nor Christianity my profession. I could never give assent to the long, complicated statements of Christian dogma.\n\n- Abraham Lincoln, Speeches and Writings, 1832-1858\n|\nA poor, who hates power, once become powerful, hates poor.\n\n- Amit Kalantri, Wealth of Words\n|\nGet off the treadmill of consumption, replication, and mediocrity. Begin lifting the weights of creativity, originality, and success.\n\n- Ryan\n|\nI love her, and that's the beginning and end of everything.\n\n- F. Scott Fitzgerald, Dear Scott, Dearest Zelda: The Love Letters of F. Scott and Zelda Fitzgerald\n|\nWhen in a relationship, a real man doesn't make his woman jealous of others, he makes others jealous of his woman.\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Unapologetically You: Reflections on Life and the Human Experience\n|\nFocus on making yourself better, not on thinking that you are better.\n\n- Bohdi Sanders, The Secrets of Worldly Wisdom: Your Key to Unlocking Success\n|\nLife is half delicious yogurt, half crap, and your job is to keep the plastic spoon in the yogurt.\n\n- Scott\n|\nAs far as I am concerned, philosophic questioning is just as likely to make you confused and depressed as it is to improve your condition.\n\n- Christopher Paolini, Brisingr\n|\nSo the freshness lives onin a lemon,in the sweet-smelling house of the rind,the proportions, arcane and acerb.\n\n- Pablo Neruda, Odes to Common Things\n|\nIf you are afraid to take a chance, take one anyway. What you don't do can create the same regrets as the mistakes you make.\n\n- Iyanla\n|\nWhen you come out of the storm, you won’t be the same person who walked in. That’s what this storm’s all about.\n\n- Haruki Murakami, Kafka on the Shore\n|\nA King will have his way in his own hall, be it folly or wisdom.\n\n- J.R.R.\n|\nTime is, in fact, a cross to bear, it passes on inexorably and remorselessly, destroying everything in its wake, save art and works of the intellect.\n\n- Jack\n|\nif love is not the answer, make sure to change the question.\n\n- Charlyn\n|\nWhen you invest your time, you are investing your life.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nThis is a wonderful day, I have never seen this one before.\n\n- Maya\n|\nIn breaking away from the familiar and the expected, you'll be forced and privileged to face greater challenges, learn harder lessons, and really get to know yourself.\n\n- Kelly Cutrone, If You Have to Cry, Go Outside: And Other Things Your Mother Never Told You\n|\nI cannot compromise my respect for your love. You can keep your love, I will keep my respect.\n\n- Amit Kalantri, Wealth of Words\n|\nA person's a person, no matter how small.\n\n- Dr. Seuss, Horton Hears a Who!\n|\nHe could feel her laughter against his chest, and at that moment he thought that there was no better feeling than making Emma Morley laugh.\n\n- David\n|\nWedded she some years, and to a manOf fifty, and such husbands are in plenty;And yet, I think, instead of such a ONE'Twere better to have TWO of five and twenty...\n\n- George Gordon Byron, Don Juan\n|\nThrough all of living have much joy and laughter, life is to be enjoyed, not just endured.\n\n- Gordon\n|\nThe only thing that belongs to us is our LIFE. Yet, we waste it in the pursuit of meaningless things that will never belong to us.\n\n- RVM\n|\nWhoever said that the past isn't dead had it backward. It's the future that's already dead, already played out.\n\n- Gayle Forman, Where She Went\n|\nFor what avail the plough or sail, or land or life, if freedom fail?\n\n- Ralph\n|\nAt the end of the story of my life, I want to say it was the best book I had ever read.\n\n- Avina\n|\nForget hard work, use Cosmic Ordering.\n\n- Stephen Richards, Cosmic Ordering: You can be successful\n|\nMr. McGregor's a nasty piece of work, isn't he? Quite the Darth Vader of children's literature.\n