 enslave, mentally or socially, a bible-reading people. The principles of the bible are the groundwork of human freedom.\n\n- Horace\n|\nA heart, once stolen, can never be taken back.\n\n- Marissa Meyer, Heartless\n|\nFor every book you buy, you should buy the time to read it.\n\n- Karl\n|\nDharma is something that one discovers, because one cannot create something that is already there.\n\n- VD.\n|\nWords are great, but actions speak louder!\n\n- Marcie Beigel, Love Your Classroom Again: Realistic Behavior Strategies for Educators\n|\nI don’t know what’s worse: to not know what you are and be happy, or to become what you’ve always wanted to be, and feel alone.\n\n- Daniel Keyes, Flowers for Algernon\n|\nThe function of a nutrient is to become transmuted, not to leave unaltered traces.\n\n- Idries Shah, The Sufis"